commText: Out come the players for the second innings. GT use their impact sub - Mohit in, Tewatia out. Interesting to see only one slip in play
Stat: Highest successful chase in IPL 2024: 183 by KKR vs RCB in Bengaluru

Kane Williamson: Nice to be out there, shame to lose Davey (Miller) for a week or two. It’s a reasonably competitive total, hopefully our bowlers can do the job in the second half. There’s a little bit there with the new ball, was trying to navigate through, a bit of sideways movement and swing on offer and hopefully, our bowlers can exploit that. (On Shubman Gill's captaincy) He has just started, a great cricket brain, what a gifted player, leads by example, he will keep growing with experience. (On the dew factor) There isn’t any at the moment which is good, so hopefully our spinners will come onto play, we have two overseas spinners in Rashid and Noor, there’s a bit of hold in the pitch and some bounce for the spinners.

Spencer Johnson would have been a great weapon on this pitch that has a lot of bounce. But they do have Noor and it'll be interesting to see. The key thing for Punjab is negotiating the new ball. This is a venue where it moves a fair bit in the powerplay. If Punjab can counter that we have a game on.

21:13 Local Time, 15:43 GMT, 21:13 IST: 199 is slightly above par on this pitch irrespective of the dew factor because of GT's bowling line-up. But they could have easily gotten more had Kane and Vijay Shankar maintained the intent. Gill bossing Ahmedabad again and batting right through. They got off to a decent start and Kane ended the powerplay on a high but they lost momentum with the field spread and Brar got Kane. Sai Sudharsan came in and hit the ball sweetly with intent and injected life back. He was outsmarted by a Harshal slower ball that cut short his promising stay. Vijay Shankar came in and tried to get going but couldn't. Gill meanwhile upped his pace and Tewatia gave yet another brilliant finish against PBKS. Rabada got two wickets. Except for the last two balls of his quota, Arshdeep was pretty good while Harshal slipped at the end.
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, poor full toss and Tewatia happily accepts the gift and slogs it to deep mid-wicket and GT finish with 199. Brilliant cameo from Tewatia

Arshdeep Singh to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, short of length into the wicket for some reason and Tewatia muscles the pull flat over mid-wicket for a one bounce four. GT get the boundary they needed to inch towards 200
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, this is outstanding bowling from Arshdeep Singh. Full and wide with third man square and it's only a single down to him as Gill tries to slice it fine
Arshdeep Singh to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, third full toss that's not placed in the gap, Tewatia livid he slogged it straight to deep mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, another low full toss just outside off stump, Gill can only drill it to long-on. Just a single
Highest individual scores in IPL 2024 87*S Gill vs PK Ahmedabad 85 S Narine vs DC Vizag 84*R Parag vs DC Jaipur 83*V Kohli vs KKR Bengaluru 82*S Samson vs LSG Jaipur
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, low full toss, Gill lofts it over cover, was soft on the shot so Brar was able to cut it off running to the left
Arshdeep Singh [3.0-0-20-0] is back into the attack

Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 3 runs, full delivery outside off stump, Gill drives it past extra-cover, Curran dives to the left at long-off and pushes it back, this gave Gill the time to steal a third and he's just home with a full length dive before the stumps were ignited

Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, lovely yorker! This time the have backward square back so Tewatia isn't only targetting the leg-side fence. So he shuffles, could only dig it out with one hand to deep cover
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, wide, short slower delivery, Tewatia moves inside the line to help it away fine but misses. Third ump checks and opines it's just above the head
Review for wide on height. Fair delivery, ah no! Just above the head

Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, FOUR, that's a ridiculous sweep shot. It's a fast bowler bowling and not a spinner mind you! Harshal Patel wants to hide the ball wide of off with fine leg and backward square leg in, Tewatia knows what's coming so he's moving across every ball. This is low full toss and he sweeps it in the gap behind square for four
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, wide, and again! Full and way outside off stump as Tewatia moves across

Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, 2 runs, short slower delivery, Tewatia pulls over square leg, valiant dive in deep. Fielder was touching the boundary cushion but he wasn't in contact with the ball at that point so it's two runs saved. Well done!
Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, wide, tries to follow Tewatia as he moves off side, but it's pitched outside the pitch. Not a no ball because it's landed beyond the stumps

Harshal Patel to Rahul Tewatia, SIX, tell him he is playing PBKS and the beast in him wakes up. Harshal Patel goes for the yorker and misses by a margin, friendly full toss to which Rahul Tewatia moves across and just whips it over deep backward square leg for a maximum
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, goes for the yorker as Gill is smacking his cutters into the wicket, it's a low full toss outside off stump, Gill drills the drive straight to deep cover

Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, oh he's sliced this over third man and seemed like a deliberate hit! Full and outside off stump, Gill clears short third man but cut off but the deep backward point fielder
Rabada to Rahul Tewatia, 1 run, pace off outside off stump, Tewatia drives to long-off
Rahul Tewatia, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Rabada to Shankar, out Caught by Harpreet Brar!! Short and slow into the wicket, Shankar tries to flat-bat this over the boundary like his partner but he's mishit this. Brar had to run in from long-off and he timed his forward dive to perfection! GT may not mind this wicket because it gets the hitters in now! Shankar c Harpreet Brar b Rabada 8(10)
Rabada to Shankar, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Gill has a word with Vijay Shankar
Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, oh in the airrr, short of long-off. Length delivery, Gill toe-ended the slog as he was rushed by th shot, escapes the mishit

Rabada to Shubman Gill, FOUR, this is an insane hit! Not much wrong with the bowler because he cramped the batter for room with a short ball but Gill is so good with a flat-batted smack straight down the ground and he's almost hit it all the way too

Rabada to Shubman Gill, SIX, runs in and bowls slot! That is a hit me ball if ever there was one. Not even pace off and Gill says oh yeah, that's what I was looking for six over wide long-on by clearing the front leg out of the way
Kagiso Rabada [3.0-0-31-1] is back into the attack
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, nice off stump yorker, Gill digs it out and keeps strike
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, lovely yorker from Harshal Patel, but Gill equally good to squeeze it past backward point for two

Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, SIX, he's flat-batted the pull, has he timed it well enough? Oh yes! Was evident Harshal Patel was going to bowl cutters into the wicket, Gill hangs back and smacks the pull over long-on to get the much needed maximum
Harshal Patel to Shankar, 1 run, slow into the wicket, Shankar only manages to flat-bat it to long-on
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, yorker on the stumps, Gill digs it out to long-on. This is really good bowling from Harshal Patel

Harshal Patel to Shankar, 1 run, short and slow down leg, Shankar gloves the pull as he plays a tad early. Gill yells out a loud yes because he wants strike badly but he's had to stretch the last few strides. Arshdeep misses the direct-hit, could have been very tight
Harshal Patel [2.0-0-12-1] is back into the attack
Looks like Gill is having trouble with the glute muscles. He's seen stretching with the physio around

Highlights (13-16 overs): - Rabada comes back and is taken for 14 runs - Gill and Sudharsan bring up the 50-run stand - Harshal Patel breaks the partnership, Sudharsan falls for 33 - Gill brings up his first fifty of the season
Arshdeep Singh to Shankar, 1 run, full and on the pads, flicked to deep mid-wicket and it's just 7 off the over. PBKS have pulled it back a bit after the previous over
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, full and angling in, Gill flicks to mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, flicked away nicely through mid-wicket, cut off in the deep and Gill says no for the third as it was risky
If Vijay Shankar doesn't get going this could put pressure on Gill. Did GT miss a trick by not sending Omarzai ahead?
Arshdeep Singh to Shankar, 1 run, short and slow, Shankar pulls, mistimes to deep backward square leg
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, goes for the yorker and bowls a low full toss, flicked to deep mid-wicket
Arshdeep Singh to Shankar, 1 run, advances and drives this full delivery to cover
Arshdeep Singh [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Shankar, 1 run, pushed to long-off

Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 3 runs, and again! It's short and down leg, fine leg is in so wonder what he's trying to do. Luckily Arshdeep moved finer at deep backward square leg and he managed to dive to the right and save a run just in time

Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, FOUR, this is a poor ball but lets get there in a moment. First fifty of the season for Gill. So this was a short delivery on the pads with not much protection in the deep behnd square on the on-side. He has packed the off-side with 3 fielders square and behind square on the off-side but bowled a freebie down leg. Gill went back to pull and placed it nicely to get four and the milestone
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, shortish delivery outside off stump, Gill chops the cut past point but gets two
Harpreet Brar to Shankar, 1 run, fired down leg, Shankar glances it through backward square leg
Harpreet Brar to Shankar, no run, shortish delivery, Shankar punches it towards point
Harpreet Brar [3.0-0-22-1] is back into the attack

Timeout! Six overs to go. They will be looking at 70 runs at least. Yes there is the dew factor here but GT defended so well with so much dew against MI and they have Mohit. 190 will be a solid total. Important that Vijay Shankar carries on the intent from Sai. PBKS will have to keep chipping away and keep this under 175
Harshal Patel to Shankar, 1 run, good length delivery on the stumps, Shankar punches it to long-on
Vijay Shankar, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! Appeal for caught behind but Sai Sudharsan walks without waiting for the finger and the ump tells the bowler he's already walked. Smart ball by Harshal Patel. Slower delivery short and angling across, Sai Sudharsan tried to guide it to third man but had to adjust the bat swing because of lack of pace, seems to have gone off the bottom of the bat to the keeper (under edge actually). Lovely little cameo from Sai though. Came out with great intent and injected life into the innings after GT slipped a bit after the powerplay. Sai Sudharsan c Jitesh Sharma b Harshal Patel 33(19) [4s-6]
Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, no run, oh play and miss! Floaty full slower delivery with mid-off up for the tease, Sai picked it and wanted a smack over wide mid-off but missed it completely
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, shortish delivery, Gill pulls it to deep mid-wicket
Harshal Patel to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, good length delivery targetting the poles, Sai Sudharsan punches it with an angled bat to deep point
Mid-off up
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ in-angler on off, Gill knocks it to long-on
Harshal Patel [1.0-0-8-0] is back into the attack
Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ short of length delivery, Gill steers wide of third man and retains strike
Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short of length angled across, Sudharsan plays a controlled pull backward of square

Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, now Sudharsan's time to go down the ground. Not quite as good as Gill's but pretty effective. Full pitcher outside off, Sudharsan lofts through the line and clears mid-off with ease
Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, short of length around off, Gill drops it with soft hands into the off-side and the pair cross over

Rabada to Shubman Gill, SIX, wow! That is the shot of the match. Nothing much wrong with the delivery - good length ball around off, Gill lofts on the rise and sends it sailing over the straight boundary. He struck that on up which suggests the pitch is getting better for batting
Rabada to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, I0$ good length ball and Sudharsan drives to sweeper cover
Kagiso Rabada [2.0-0-17-1] is back into the attack

Highlights (7-12 overs): - Brar keeps it quiet after powerplay - Harshal starts with a decent over but concedes a boundary to Gill - Rabada gets Saha for the fourth time - Brar has Williamson caught at backward point - Sai Sudharsan shows intent straightaway - Raza taken for 14 runs in his 2nd over
Raza to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, sliding in with the angle, Sudharsan works it to deep mid-wicket

Raza to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, Sudharsan is on fire. He's taken a liking towards Raza. This is short and Sudharsan is quick to pounce, he pulls it in front of square and splits the two fielders in the deep
Raza to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, drifting down leg, Sudharsan sits down and nails the sweep behind square on the leg-side
Raza to Shubman Gill, 1 run, comes down the track and is met by a short of length delivery, pulled to deep square leg

Raza to Shubman Gill, FOUR, smashed! Raza attempts the back of the hand wrong 'un and drags it short, Gill stays back and slaps it straight down the ground. He had the width to free his hands and he went straight
Raza to Shubman Gill, no run, quicker and fuller, Gill pushes it back to Raza
Sam Curran to Shubman Gill, 1 run, loopy slower ball on off, Gill goes hard on the drive and mistimes it to long-on
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, short and at the body, Sudharsan pulls and picks out Harshal at long leg
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, that's a poor delivery. Strays onto leg-stump, Sudharsan plays a neat leg glance and the ball races away to the fine leg fence
Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, no run, angled in from short of length, Sudharsan is cramped on the pull and the ball hits him on the thigh
Sam Curran to Shubman Gill, 1 run, slower ball on leg-stump, Gill nudges it square on the leg-side

Sam Curran to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, good length ball around off, Sudharsan angles it behind square on the off-side and wanted a second, but Gill is not interested. The second was on and Gill was slow in his first run
Sam Curran [1.0-0-10-0] is back into the attack
Raza to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, another short of length delivery, Sudharsan pulls to deep mid-wicket
Raza to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, short of length and slides in, Sudharsan rocks back and nails the pull in front of square, between deep mid-wicket and long-on
Raza to Sai Sudharsan, no run, slower and flighted around off, Sudharsan defends it back to Raza
Raza to Shubman Gill, 1 run, once more bowled short and into the wicket, Gill pulls close to deep mid-wicket
Raza to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, drifts in with the angle, Sudharsan tucks it to the vacant mid-wicket region
Round the wicket to the left hander
Raza to Shubman Gill, 1 run, short of length on off, Gill pulls to deep mid-wicket
Sikandar Raza, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, FOUR, this time there's no deny Sudharsan a boundary. Sliding across from round the wicket, he uses that angle and opens the bat face to steer it through short third
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, drifts in with the angle, Gill works it to long-on

Harpreet Brar to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, fine stop from Rabada. Full pitcher outside off, Sudharsan drives in front of square through extra cover, Rabada gets around from long-off and slides, makes a one handed save
Sai Sudharsan, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Harpreet Brar to Williamson, out Caught by Bairstow!! Brar strikes! Much needed for Punjab and it comes right after the break. Williamson would be disappointed because this was not a wicket-taking delivery. Short and outside off, Williamson cuts it straight to backward point and Bairstow didn't move an inch. He reverse cups it safely. It was the extra bounce that did not allow Williamson to keep the cut down. Williamson c Bairstow b Harpreet Brar 26(22) [4s-4]
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, THATS OUT!! Caught!!
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, FOUR, lovely shot! Williamson comes down the track, gives himself room and drives inside out past cover. Brar bowled it quicker but Williamson was up for it
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, no run, I0$ delivery that is fraction short, Williamson chops it to backward point

Timeout! This is a solid start from Gujarat Titans. They lost Saha early but these two have gone about business in a smooth manner. The surface does have something in it for the bowlers and a score around 170-180 would be competitive.
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, no run, I0$ fullish delivery outside off, Gill punches firmly to cover
Harshal Patel to Williamson, 1 run, slower back of a length delivery, Williamson whips it to deep mid-wicket
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ good length ball on off, Gill knocks it to long-on
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, FOUR, short and pace on, the line is outside off and Gill says thank you very much, he does not bother to keep the cut down and goes over the backward point region
Harshal Patel to Williamson, 1 run, I0$ fullish delivery, Williamson shimmies down and mistimes the drive wide of mid-off
Harshal Patel to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ short of length delivery, Gill pulls to deep mid-wicket
Harshal Patel, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, no run, I0$ delivery attacking the stumps, Williamson knocks it to cover
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, no run, I0$ flighted on off, Williamson pushes it straight to cover
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, 2 runs, flighted close to off, Williamson chips it over cover and Gill races back for the second. Good batting and running
Harpreet Brar to Williamson, 2 runs, arm-ball that skids in, Williamson glances it to short fine and Prabhsimran makes a mess, gifts a couple
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ delivery that is shortened, Gill works it wide of mid-wicket
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, no run, tossed up around off, Gill eases it to cover
Harpreet Brar [1.0-0-7-0] is back into the attack

Highlights (1-6 overs): - PBKS bowl left-arm spin as matchup to Gill but Gill smacks a six - Saha successfully overturns a poor LBW decision off the bowling of Arshdeep - Rabada gets Saha for the fourth time - Arshdeep finds the edge off Gill but slip was vacant - Kane takes Rabada for four, but still a quiet over - Curran starts the over well but Kane manages to find two fours
Sam Curran to Williamson, no run, charges down and is cramped by a short of length delivery, chops the cut towards cover-point
Sam Curran to Williamson, no run, angled in on off-stump, Williamson plays it with soft hands behind the wicket

Sam Curran to Williamson, FOUR, classical shot! This is vintage Williamson. Another slower ball from Curran and this time Williamson was up for it, he has a good stride forward and caresses the drive wide of mid-off

Sam Curran to Williamson, 2 runs, in the air and safe. I0$ another off-pace delivery and Williamson is deceived completely, but luckily for him his checked loft clears the off-side field and lands safely

Sam Curran to Williamson, FOUR, I0$ slower ball on a driving length, Williamson is drawn into the shot and ekes out an outside edge through the vacant slip cordon. Third man was also inside the ring..
Round the wicket to Williamson

Sam Curran to Shubman Gill, leg byes, 1 run, nips back in from short of length, Gill misses the tuck and the ball lobs off the thigh pad to backward point, Williamson calls for a quick single and they make it with ease
Sam Curran, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
What happened there? Gill moves away and Curran still bowls the ball. Some issue behind the bowler and he informs the same to umpire Kulkarni
Rabada to Williamson, no run, short of length delivery on off, Williamson gets on top of the bounce and blocks
Rabada to Williamson, no run, I0$ back of a length around off, Williamson defends it back to Rabada
Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, attacks the stumps, Gill plays it with soft hands in front of mid-on and quickly crosses over
Rabada to Williamson, 1 run, fullish delivery in the channel, Williamson inside halves the block to backward square
Rabada to Williamson, FOUR, lovely shot! Williamson advances and Rabada drags the length back, but the former just eases the drive on the rise in front of square and the timing takes care of the rest
Rabada to Williamson, no run, I0$ fuller and close to off, Williamson defends with soft hands to point

Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, FOUR, edged but Gill knew what he was doing. There was no slip in place for him and third man was inside the ring, so he uses the angle going across him and steers it off the outside edge through the vacant cordon
Arshdeep Singh to Williamson, 1 run, angled outside off, Williamson opens the bat face and guides it to third man
Arshdeep Singh to Williamson, no run, bit of extra bounce. I0$ good length ball and Williamson was coming forward to defend, he's surprised by the extra lift and is beaten on the outside edge
Lowest SR in Powerplay since IPL 2022 (100+ balls) 76.38 K Williamson 107.63 H Pandya 110.61 Sai Sudarshan 111.74 KL Rahul 111.92 D Hooda

Arshdeep Singh to Williamson, no run, I0$ inswinger on off-stump, Williamson stays rooted to the crease and ekes out an inside edge onto the back pad. Stifled appeal for LBW from Arshdeep but there was a clear edge
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 1 run, I0$ short and outside off, Gill cuts and there's protection at deep point
Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, no run, fullish delivery angled across, Gill prods forward and defends to cover
Kane Williamson, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Saha vs Rabada in IPL Five innings 33 balls 51 runs Four dismissals SR 154.54

Rabada to Saha, out Caught by Dhawan!! Rabada draws first blood. I0$ angled in and the ball lands around good length, Saha thinks he can flick it over the leg-side field and closes the bat face, he's a tad early and the leading edge goes straight up, Dhawan settles under it near extra cover. He takes the catch and does the thigh-five. This is the fourth time Rabada has got rid of Saha. Saha c Dhawan b Rabada 11(13) [4s-2]
Rabada to Saha, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Rabada to Saha, FOUR, width on offer and Saha does not need a second invitation, he goes aerial with his drive and clears the infield, not quite off the middle but the ball has enough to trickle into the rope
Rabada to Saha, no run, in-slanter from short of length, Saha jams it onto the pad and the ball rolls to the off-side
Rabada to Shubman Gill, 1 run, back of a length and bit of extra bounce, Gill closes the bat face and the leading edge rolls to point

Rabada to Shubman Gill, FOUR, shot! I0$ good length ball on middle, Gill plants his front foot across and clips it behind square on the leg-side, the pace of Rabada takes the ball to the fence in a jiffy
Rabada to Saha, 1 run, I0$ back of a length around off, Saha plays it with soft hands into the off-side and the pair quickly switch ends
Rabada to Saha, wide, starts with a wide down leg, Saha misses the glance and Jitesh dives to glove the ball
Kagiso Rabada, right-arm fast, comes into the attack

Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, 2 runs, charges down and is met by a short of length delivery, pulls it behind square and is denied a boundary by a diving Shashank Singh, he gets around from fine leg and puts in the dive to keep it to a couple
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, 1 run, back of a length around off, Saha plays it with soft hands towards backward point and crosses over

Arshdeep Singh to Saha, FOUR, that's a gift from Arshdeep. Full delivery on leg-stump, Saha does not go hard on the flick, just chips it over the leg-side infield and allows the outfield to do the rest
Arshdeep Singh to Saha, no run, on a length and shapes in, but stops a bit, Saha checks his shot and sends it to mid-wicket

Arshdeep Singh to Saha, leg byes, FOUR, Jitesh Sharma gives chase and stumbles because of his pads. Swinging down leg, Saha misses the glance and the ball deflects off the thigh pad to fine leg, Jitesh sprints behind but trips and falls over before getting to the ball

Arshdeep Singh to Saha, no run, Saha survives. That was a poor decision from umpire Vineet Kulkarni. He has a wry smile as he's made to change his decision. Inswinger and Saha is beaten on the inside edge, struck above the pad and the ball was going over. Arshdeep was not even confident in his appeal but umpire Kulkarni had the finger up in a jiffy

Gujarat review! Saha is given out LBW and he's challenged it. Umpire Vineet Kulkarni's finger went up in a flash. Height was an issue there. Saha even shows Gill where the ball hit him - above the pad and close to the thigh pad. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball-tracking shows it to be missing. Not Out..
Arshdeep Singh, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, SIX, lovely shot! Weakness against left-arm spin? Nah says Gill. He shimmies down the wicket, converts it into a half volley and smokes it straight back over, the ball lands flush on the ad cushions
Harpreet Brar to Shubman Gill, no run, I0$ fullish delivery and Gill pushes it firmly to cover
Harpreet Brar to Saha, 1 run, drifts in with the angle, Saha nudges it to square leg and there's a bit of hesitation, but Gill makes it
Harpreet Brar to Saha, no run, I0$ back of a length delivery, Saha stays back and knocks it to cover
Harpreet Brar to Saha, no run, throws it up wider of off-stump, Saha drives and picks out extra cover
Harpreet Brar to Saha, no run, slower and short of length, stops a bit, Saha waits and knocks it back to Brar
Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Harpreet Brar will open the attack
